I TOLD YOU
NOT TO MOVE, CANDY.

04:37.904 --> 04:40.273
WAR, PLEASE.
PLEASE.

04:40.273 --> 04:43.076
YOU KNOW
HOW THIS GOES, CANDY.

04:43.076 --> 04:46.513
I CAN'T LET YOU LIVE.

04:46.513 --> 04:48.181
I HAVE A REPUTATION.

04:48.181 --> 04:50.183
I KNOW.

04:50.183 --> 04:51.685
BUT NOBODY KNOWS.

04:51.685 --> 04:54.020
‐I KNOW.
‐WAR, PLEASE.

04:54.020 --> 04:56.890
I KNOW, CANDY.

04:56.890 --> 04:59.225
PLEASE.

04:59.225 --> 05:02.035
SEE, THIS WHAT HAPPENS

05:02.035 --> 05:06.006
WHEN FOOLS TRY TO MAKE
ME LOOK LIKE A FOOL.

05:06.006 --> 05:09.109
WHAT CAN I DO FOR YOU?
HUH?

05:09.109 --> 05:12.946
TELL ME.
WHAT CAN I DO?

05:12.946 --> 05:14.447
WHAT CAN YOU DO?

05:14.447 --> 05:18.251
ANYTHING.
ANYTHING.

05:20.954 --> 05:24.124
LET ME THINK.

05:24.124 --> 05:25.592
YOU THINK YOU GOT
2 MILLION DOLLARS WORTH

05:25.592 --> 05:27.761
BETWEEN YOUR LEGS?

05:27.761 --> 05:29.530
THAT'S A DIME A DOZEN,
WHERE I COME FROM.

05:29.530 --> 05:32.198
$2 MILLION?

05:32.198 --> 05:34.034
SEE,
THE WAY I FIGURE IT,

05:34.034 --> 05:35.268
IS YOU SPENT
2 AND A HALF

05:35.268 --> 05:38.104
ON ALL THESE HOUSES
AND THAT TOW YARD.

05:38.104 --> 05:39.573
I WANT
A MIL AND A HALF,

05:39.573 --> 05:41.474
AND THAT'S GIVING YOU
A DISCOUNT.

05:41.474 --> 05:44.177
YOU GOT $4 MILLION,
RIGHT?

05:44.177 --> 05:48.815
YOU GOT
$4 MILLION, RIGHT?

05:48.815 --> 05:49.783
YES.

05:49.783 --> 05:51.585
DID YOU SAY YES?

05:51.585 --> 05:53.053
YES.

05:53.053 --> 05:55.756
$4 MILLION,

05:55.756 --> 05:59.059
AND YOU LIED TO ME
AND TOLD ME IT WAS $400,000,

05:59.059 --> 06:01.267
AND THAT'S
A FEDERAL JUDGE.

06:01.267 --> 06:03.369
I WENT OUT
ON A LIMB FOR YOU, CANDY.

06:03.369 --> 06:05.939
YOU LOST YOUR MIND?

06:05.939 --> 06:08.074
I WANT $1.5.

06:10.343 --> 06:11.912
OKAY.

06:11.912 --> 06:15.115
I WANT IT NOW.

06:15.115 --> 06:17.684
I DON'T HAVE IT NOW.

06:17.684 --> 06:20.120
WAIT!
WAR.

06:20.120 --> 06:22.022
WHY DON'T YOU HAVE IT?

06:22.022 --> 06:24.090
HMM?
YOU SPEND ALL OF IT?

06:24.090 --> 06:25.325
NO.

06:25.325 --> 06:26.860
THEN WHERE IS IT?

06:26.860 --> 06:29.162
‐IT WAS TAKEN FROM ME.
‐NOW, SEE?

06:29.162 --> 06:30.864
THAT'S THE STUFF
THAT MAKES ME MAD AS ‐‐

06:30.864 --> 06:32.899
[ GUNSHOT, GLASS SHATTERS ]

06:41.141 --> 06:42.676
IT'S CANDY.

06:45.478 --> 06:49.850
THAT DON'T MEAN NOTHING
RIGHT NOW.

06:49.850 --> 06:54.655
YOU'RE A TRAITOR...
AND A LIAR.

06:54.655 --> 06:56.256
YOU BROKE THE CODE...

06:59.192 --> 07:00.967
AND YOU BROKE MY HEART.

07:03.469 --> 07:06.339
I'LL GET THE MONEY.

07:06.339 --> 07:07.674
I WAS MARKED.

07:07.674 --> 07:10.376
‐WHAT?
‐YES.

07:10.376 --> 07:12.178
BY THIS GUY NAMED OSCAR.

07:12.178 --> 07:15.481
I WAS MARKED,
AND ONCE I‐I‐I GET TO HIM,

07:15.481 --> 07:17.518
I WILL GET YOU YOUR MONEY.

07:17.518 --> 07:18.952
NO. NO.

07:18.952 --> 07:20.687
NO, NO, NO, NO, NO, NO.
NO. NO. NO. NO.

07:20.687 --> 07:21.588
YOU'RE LYING.

07:21.588 --> 07:23.289
NO. I'M NOT.

07:23.289 --> 07:25.759
I'M NOT.

07:25.759 --> 07:28.562
I JUST NEED A ‐‐
A FEW DAYS.

07:28.562 --> 07:29.896
‐WHAT?
‐YEAH.

07:29.896 --> 07:32.566
A FEW DAYS, CANDY?

07:32.566 --> 07:34.701
‐A WEEK?
‐A WEEK?

07:34.701 --> 07:37.370
YOU GONNA HAVE MY MONEY
IN SEVEN DAYS?

07:37.370 --> 07:38.639
YES.

07:38.639 --> 07:40.440
OKAY, THEN.

07:42.743 --> 07:45.979
ON THE EIGHTH DAY,
YOUR ASS IS DEAD.

07:49.182 --> 07:50.917
WAR.

07:50.917 --> 07:53.053
WHAT?

07:53.053 --> 07:55.656
CAN YOU HELP ME?

07:55.656 --> 07:58.659
HELP YOU DO WHAT?

07:58.659 --> 08:02.135
HE'S TOO BIG
FOR ME TO LIFT.

08:02.135 --> 08:05.038
HE'S GOT TO DISAPPEAR.

08:05.038 --> 08:06.873
SURE.

08:06.873 --> 08:09.543
WHAT DO YOU
WANT ME TO DO?

08:09.543 --> 08:11.177
WELL, I GOT
TO GET HIM OUT OF HERE,

08:11.177 --> 08:12.646
BUT MY NEIGHBOR
ACROSS THE STREET

08:12.646 --> 08:16.583
IS WATCHING
EVERYTHING I DO.

08:16.583 --> 08:18.351
OKAY.

08:18.351 --> 08:20.286
REALLY?

08:20.286 --> 08:23.156
‐SURE, GIRL.
‐THANK YOU.

08:23.156 --> 08:26.426
OH, WAIT,
YOU ONLY GET ONE FAVOR.

08:26.426 --> 08:28.695
ONE IS TO LIVE
FOR SEVEN DAYS,

08:28.695 --> 08:31.364
OR THE OTHER IS TO HELP YOU
WITH THIS FOOL.

08:31.364 --> 08:33.133
NOW,
WHICH ONE YOU WANT?

08:35.301 --> 08:39.205
I'LL...TAKE CARE
OF THIS MYSELF.

08:39.205 --> 08:40.574
AND MY MONEY?

08:40.574 --> 08:44.144
AND YOUR MONEY, I'LL ‐‐
I'LL GET YOU YOUR MONEY.

08:44.144 --> 08:46.179
‐OKAY.
‐OKAY.

08:54.287 --> 08:56.056
I LOVE YOU.

08:58.058 --> 09:00.634
YEAH.
LOVE YOU, TOO.

09:03.103 --> 09:04.871
YOU KNOW,
ON SECOND THOUGHT...

09:04.871 --> 09:08.942
NOW, BEFORE I LEAVE,
COME GET ON THIS.

09:54.420 --> 09:55.756
HERE YOU GO.

09:55.756 --> 09:59.192
GIVE IT TO HER AND GET THAT
TO THE LAB RIGHT AWAY, PLEASE.

09:59.192 --> 10:02.368
‐THIS WON'T TAKE LONG.
‐THANK YOU.

10:02.368 --> 10:04.037
SO,
WHAT DO I DO NOW?

10:04.037 --> 10:06.072
WELL, UH,
YOU CAN GO HOME,

10:06.072 --> 10:08.742
AND I WILL CALL YOU AS SOON
AS I GET THE LAB RESULTS.

10:08.742 --> 10:10.310
‐THEY'RE GOOD.
‐WELL, GOOD.

10:10.310 --> 10:13.714
I BELIEVE YOU.

10:13.714 --> 10:16.783
SO, WHAT'S GOING ON
WITH MY PARENTS?

10:16.783 --> 10:19.586
THEY'RE OKAY.

10:19.586 --> 10:21.688
OKAY?

10:21.688 --> 10:24.157
ARE YOU WORRIED
ABOUT THEM?

10:24.157 --> 10:27.460
NO.
NOT AT ALL.

10:27.460 --> 10:29.362
CAN THEY GET OUT SOON?

10:29.362 --> 10:31.364
WELL, I'M TRYING
TO KEEP THEM IN

10:31.364 --> 10:32.666
UNTIL YOU GET OUT
OF THE HOUSE,

10:32.666 --> 10:35.602
BUT MORE THAN LIKELY,
YOUR MOM WILL GET OUT FIRST.

10:35.602 --> 10:36.737
OKAY.

10:36.737 --> 10:39.873
THEN, I GUESS AFTER
THE DRUG TEST CHECKS OUT

10:39.873 --> 10:42.543
AND WE VERIFY
YOUR REHAB STAY,

10:42.543 --> 10:45.211
THEN WE'LL GET THE DOCUMENTS
AND GET YOUR FUNDS RELEASED.

10:45.211 --> 10:46.780
BUT, YOU KNOW,
YOU SHOULD CHECK INTO A HOTEL

10:46.780 --> 10:48.481
UNTIL YOU GET A PLACE.

10:48.481 --> 10:51.585
‐OKAY.
‐DO YOU HAVE ONE IN MIND?

10:51.585 --> 10:53.086
THE ONLY NICE ONE IN TOWN.

10:53.086 --> 10:54.855
‐WHERE'S THAT?
‐SARANDON.

10:54.855 --> 10:57.190
OH, YEAH, RIGHT.
OKAY.

10:57.190 --> 10:59.025
WHEN DID
THE HARRINGTONS GET OUT?

11:01.034 --> 11:02.603
I'M NOT SURE.

11:05.338 --> 11:09.209
DOES JEFFERY
HAVE A DRINKING PROBLEM?

11:09.209 --> 11:10.877
NO.
WHY DO YOU ASK?

11:10.877 --> 11:12.613
HE WAS ARRESTED
FOR D.U.I.

11:12.613 --> 11:14.414
‐JEFFERY?
‐YES.

11:14.414 --> 11:15.616
IT'S NOT LIKE HIM AT ALL.

11:15.616 --> 11:16.950
HE MUST BE HAVING
A HARD TIME WITH THIS,

11:16.950 --> 11:18.585
THAT'S ALL.

11:18.585 --> 11:21.522
WELL, I‐I'M GOING
TO TALK TO HIM TODAY.

11:23.389 --> 11:24.925
DOES HE NEED ME
TO BAIL HIM OUT OR ANYTHING?

11:24.925 --> 11:28.261
NO, NO.
I‐I'LL TAKE CARE OF IT.

11:28.261 --> 11:29.262
OKAY.

11:29.262 --> 11:32.298
SO, GO HOME
AND START PACKING.

11:32.298 --> 11:33.900
AS SOON AS ALL
OF THIS CHECKS OUT,

11:33.900 --> 11:36.069
I'LL FAX THE PAPERS
TO THE BANK.

11:38.404 --> 11:40.040
OKAY.
THANK YOU.

11:40.040 --> 11:41.474
THANK YOU, WYATT.

11:43.710 --> 11:45.211
I‐I REALLY APPRECIATE IT.

11:45.211 --> 11:49.149
I MEAN...
YOU'RE AN ANGEL FOR ME.

11:51.451 --> 11:53.453
‐I'LL SEE YOU.
‐YEAH.

12:02.669 --> 12:04.571
‐MS. SALLISON?
‐YES?

12:04.571 --> 12:06.840
‐WE HAVE A PROBLEM?
‐WHAT?

12:06.840 --> 12:08.642
TAKE A LOOK.

12:11.712 --> 12:13.313
WHERE DID THIS
COME FROM?

12:29.863 --> 12:31.998
[ CLEARS THROAT ]
WHERE DID THIS COME FROM?

12:33.534 --> 12:34.668
HI.

12:37.771 --> 12:40.073
WHAT IS THIS?

12:40.073 --> 12:41.775
YOU'RE A D.A.
YOU SEE IT.

12:41.775 --> 12:44.044
HE IS UNDER ARREST.

12:44.044 --> 12:46.513
NOT ANYMORE.
THAT'S FROM JUDGE KATZ.

12:46.513 --> 12:47.514
I KNOW THAT JUDGE.

12:47.514 --> 12:50.183
THEN YOU KNOW
HOW SERIOUS HE IS.

12:50.183 --> 12:51.885
WAIT, WHO ARE YOU?

12:51.885 --> 12:53.486
I'M MAGGIE DAY.

12:53.486 --> 12:55.622
WHO ARE YOU TO HIM?

12:55.622 --> 12:58.058
I'M DAVID'S
CAMPAIGN MANAGER.

12:58.058 --> 13:01.835
NO, YOU'RE THE CAMPAIGN MANAGER
FOR THE ENTIRE CAMPAIGN.

13:01.835 --> 13:04.370
YES.

13:04.370 --> 13:07.574
WHY WOULD THE JUDGE RELEASE
DAVID AND NOT JIM, TOO?

13:07.574 --> 13:09.142
WE DIDN'T ASK
FOR JIM'S RELEASE.

13:09.142 --> 13:11.545
‐WHY NOT?
‐I'M HERE FOR DAVID.

13:11.545 --> 13:15.048
WHY WOULD THE JUDGE
RELEASE DAVID ALONE?

13:15.048 --> 13:16.316
DAVID HAS NOTHING
TO DO WITH THIS.

13:16.316 --> 13:18.051
‐HOW DO YOU KNOW?
‐BECAUSE I KNOW HIM.

13:18.051 --> 13:20.621
‐YOU KNOW HIM.
‐YES, AND I ALSO KNOW JIM.

13:20.621 --> 13:21.922
HOW WELL
DO YOU KNOW HIM?

13:21.922 --> 13:23.256
AS I JUST SAID,
I'M JIM'S CAMPAIGN MA‐‐

13:23.256 --> 13:24.825
DAVID.

13:24.825 --> 13:27.594
I WORK WITH HIM.

13:31.632 --> 13:33.399
WHAT?

13:33.399 --> 13:35.769
HE CAN'T BE RELEASED
JUST YET.

13:35.769 --> 13:37.170
OKAY.

13:37.170 --> 13:38.438
LISTEN, LADY, YOU ARE GETTING
WAY TOO CLOSE TO THE FIRE.

13:38.438 --> 13:39.740
THIS IS FROM A JUDGE,

13:39.740 --> 13:42.142
AND I WILL DRAG HIM DOWN HERE
RIGHT NOW IF I HAVE TO,

13:42.142 --> 13:43.810
AND I PROMISE YOU IT'S NOT
GOING TO BE PRETTY.

13:43.810 --> 13:45.979
SO WHY DON'T YOU
DO YOURSELF A FAVOR ‐‐

13:45.979 --> 13:48.715
GO GET DAVID HARRINGTON,
LET HIM OUT RIGHT NOW

13:48.715 --> 13:51.785
OR YOUR LIFE IS GONNA CHANGE
RATHER QUICKLY.

13:51.785 --> 13:53.386
JIM IS THE ONE
RUNNING FOR GOVERNOR,

13:53.386 --> 13:54.821
SO HE SHOULD BE THE ONE ‐‐

13:54.821 --> 13:56.590
DAVID HARRINGTON.
NOW.

13:59.325 --> 14:02.368
I HAVE AN INTERVIEW,
SO YOU SHOULD HAVE A SEAT.

14:02.368 --> 14:03.670
IT MAY TAKE A WHILE.

14:03.670 --> 14:05.471
IF HE'S NOT OUT HERE
IN 15 MINUTES ‐‐

14:05.471 --> 14:07.407
OH,
IT WON'T BE THAT SOON.

14:07.407 --> 14:09.375
THEN I'LL BE ON THE PHONE
WITH THE ATTORNEY GENERAL.

14:09.375 --> 14:11.645
WOULD YOU LIKE
TO USE MY PHONE?

14:15.315 --> 14:16.550
HOW LONG WILL IT TAKE?

14:16.550 --> 14:19.285
AS LONG AS IT TAKES.

14:19.285 --> 14:21.087
GREAT.

14:21.087 --> 14:22.455
HAVE A SEAT.

14:22.455 --> 14:24.257
HMM.

14:31.197 --> 14:33.199
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

14:34.735 --> 14:37.270
OH, THIS IS RIDICULOUS.

14:37.270 --> 14:38.639
I KNOW.

14:41.174 --> 14:43.510
‐MRS. CRYER.
‐YES?

14:43.510 --> 14:45.612
RIGHT THIS WAY.

14:45.612 --> 14:46.847
WHERE IS SHE GOING?

14:46.847 --> 14:49.249
THE D. A. WOULD LIKE
TO SPEAK WITH HER.

14:49.249 --> 14:51.451
WELL, SHE HAS NOTHING
TO SAY TO THE D. A.

14:51.451 --> 14:52.519
WELL, TELL HER THAT.

14:52.519 --> 14:54.220
SHE IS BEING
REPRESENTED BY COUNSEL.

14:54.220 --> 14:57.691
LADY, I'M JUST AN OFFICER.
I DON'T CARE.

14:57.691 --> 15:00.226
‐KATHERYN.
‐I KNOW. I KNOW.

15:00.226 --> 15:01.201
NO.
DON'T SAY ANYTHING.

15:01.201 --> 15:02.703
NO MATTER WHAT SHE SAYS ‐‐
‐I KNOW.

15:02.703 --> 15:04.605
NO, I MEAN IT, KATHERYN.
DON'T SAY ANYTHING.

15:04.605 --> 15:07.273
VERONICA,
YOU UNDERESTIMATE ME.

15:07.273 --> 15:10.210
JUST KNOW SHE'S GONNA TRY
TO ENTRAP YOU.

15:10.210 --> 15:11.678
OH, I KNOW.

15:11.678 --> 15:13.747
WE'RE BEING DENIED OUR RIGHT
TO A PHONE CALL

15:13.747 --> 15:15.348
AND I WANT IT ON RECORD.

15:15.348 --> 15:17.651
‐WE'RE WORKING ON IT.
‐AH!

15:17.651 --> 15:20.253
